claim.claim-text:
A haptic display device comprising:
a substrate (110);
a plurality of scan lines (121) disposed over the substrate (110) and configured to transfer a scan signal;
a plurality of data lines (171) on an interlayer insulating layer (160) electrically insulating the data lines (171) from the scan lines (121, the data lines (171) being configured to transfer a data signal, wherein the data lines (171) cross the scan lines (121);
a protective layer (180) on the interlayer insulating layer (160) and the data lines (171),
a plurality of haptic control lines (410, 420, 430, 440) electrically insulated from the scan lines (121) or the data lines (171) and configured to transfer a haptic signal;
at each crossing of the data lines (171) with the scan lines (121), a first electrode (190) on the protective layer (180);
a barrier rib (350) on the protective layer (180),
;a second electrode (270) atop the barrier rib (350) and facing the first electrode (190); and
for each haptic control line (410, 420, 430, 440), at least one haptic member (510, 520, 531, 532, 533, 541, 542, 543) provided between the respective haptic control line (410, 420, 430, 440) and one of either the scan lines (121), or the data lines (171), or the first electrodes (190) or the second electrode (270).

A haptic display device according to one of the preceding claims, the device further comprising:
a switching thin film transistor (10) electrically connected to a selected one of the scan lines (121) and the corresponding data line (171);
a driving transistor (20) electrically connected to the switching thin film transistor (10) and a selected one of the driving power lines (172);
wherein the first electrode (190) is electrically connected to the driving transistor (20); and
an organic light emitting diode (300) is disposed on the first electrode (190).
